data.value: The point of the game is to live as long as you can. Your Sim character has a hunger, bladder , energy, and hygiene progress bar that will keep track of your Sims needs. Your job is to fulfill your Sims needs to keep them living as long as possible. Before you start playing you will be prompted to choose a house for your Sim to live in. Once you have chosen your house, that will be where you can fulfill their needs. You can either walk into your house or click on the floating diamond above your house for the option buttons to appear where you cando things like, "Eat Dinner" , or "Go to Bed." Completing these actions will reset your progress bars. If you fail to keep track of your Sims needs, they will either die or lose money. As well as keeping your Sim's needs in control, you are also responsible for keeping your Sim entertained. There are many different stores and places for your Sim to go to. To travel to these placesall you must simply do is walk into them. Once you walk into them the option buttons will appear. To walk around the Sim map you use your up, down, left, and right arrow keys. If youaccidently run into a builidng you cannot move until you have selected an option. If this happens just click exit and continue on your way. At the beginning of the game you will also be prompted to choose a career. You can go to your job and earn money every 100 seconds. To entertain your Sim to the fullest amount you can click on your Sim for some more fun options.Simply the point of the game is to live your Sims life.
